fullDescription.intro:
This node takes a route, encoded as a WKT Linestring, and matches it to a sequence of traversed OSM road segments, that can be analyzed
        	   by the coverage analyzer nodes in KNOT. 
        	   The node requires that the input table contains three columns:


id, an integer that identifies the owner of the route;

begin_at, a LocalDateTime that pinpoints the starting time of the route; 

the_geom, a String containing a WKT-like representation of the route.

ports.inPort:
A table containining data about routes. 
        It must contain the following columns:


id, an integer that identifies the owner of the route;

begin_at, a LocalDateTime that pinpoints the starting time of the route; 

the_geom, a String containing a WKT-like representation of the route.
